  "content": "\n# Walk-In Shower Cost in Chandler, AZ - 2025 Installation Pricing\n\nWalk-in showers have become the centerpiece of modern bathroom design. Homeowners are replacing outdated acrylic tubs and metal-framed enclosures with open, spacious tiled showers. In Chandler, Arizona, a custom walk-in shower is not only a functional upgrade for daily comfort and safety, but it is also one of the most reliable ways to boost home value. \n\nIn this guide, we provide a detailed analysis of current 2025 installation costs, material choices, and labor rates in the East Valley.\n\n---\n\n## Average Cost of Walk-In Showers in Chandler\n\nThe cost to install a custom walk-in shower in Chandler ranges from **$6,000 to over $18,000**, with the average project landing around **$9,500**. The final price depends on the size of the shower, the complexity of the plumbing, the quality of the tile, and the type of glass enclosure.\n\nFor general pricing information on shower projects, you can also check out our standalone [walk-in shower cost](/walk-in-shower-cost/) guide.\n\nHere is a breakdown of average costs by shower configuration:\n\n| Shower Type | Average Cost Range | Key Specifications | Typical Materials |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Prefabricated Kit** | $5,500 – $8,000 | Acrylic or fiberglass pan and wall panels; sliding framed door. | Acrylic base, standard chrome trim. |\n| **Standard Tiled Shower** | $8,500 – $13,000 | Custom sloped base, porcelain tile walls, built-in niche, semi-frameless glass. | Schluter waterproofing, porcelain tile. |\n| **Zero-Threshold Curbless** | $12,000 – $18,000+ | Recessed subfloor, seamless entry, high-flow linear drain, frameless glass. | Custom tile pan, 3/8\" glass, epoxy grout. |\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Cost Breakdown of Shower Components\n\n### 1. Demolition and Site Preparation ($800 – $1,500)\nTearing out an old shower or bathtub down to the framing studs is the first step. This cost includes:\n*   Hauling away old tile, plaster, cast-iron tubs, and metal frames.\n*   Disposal fees and debris containment.\n*   Vetting the wall studs for water damage or dry rot.\n\n### 2. Plumbing Modifications & Valves ($1,200 – $2,500)\nOlder homes in Chandler may need plumbing upgrades to meet current codes:\n*   **Drain Expansion:** Upgrading the drain line from 1.5 inches to 2 inches is required when converting a tub to a shower.\n*   **Shower Valve:** Installing a pressure-balancing valve to prevent temperature surges.\n*   **Fixture Additions:** Adding rainfall showerheads or dual body jets.\n\n### 3. Substrate & Waterproofing ($1,500 – $2,500)\nA shower is only as durable as the waterproofing underneath the tile.\n*   **Schluter-KERDI System:** We use a complete Schluter membrane system to create a vapor-tight seal. This protects your home's wood framing from steam damage and mold. Learn more about our technical approach in our guide to [why we use Schluter-KERDI waterproofing](/blog/why-we-use-schluter-kerdi-waterproofing-chandler/).\n\n### 4. Custom Tile & Grout ($2,500 – $5,000)\nTile selection has a major impact on both the aesthetics and cost:\n*   **Porcelain Tile:** The standard choice for durability and ease of cleaning in Arizona.\n*   **Specialty Tile:** Marble, travertine, or custom glass accents require extra care during setting.\n*   **Grout Upgrade:** Upgrading to non-porous epoxy grout is highly recommended to resist hard water mineral scale.\n\n### 5. Glass Enclosures ($1,500 – $3,500)\n*   **Frameless Glass:** 3/8-inch or 1/2-inch tempered glass panels secured with heavy brass clips.\n*   **Coating:** Factory-applied hydrophobic coatings (like EnduroShield) are essential to prevent calcium spots.\n\n---\n\n## Specific Cost Factors for Chandler Arizona Homes\n\n### 1. Hard Water Protection\nChandler water has a high mineral content, averaging over 300 mg/L of dissolved calcium. This mineral buildup will ruin standard grout and cloud glass panels:\n*   Investing in **epoxy grout** saves money in the long run by preventing stains.\n*   Opt for brushed finishes (like nickel or brass) rather than polished chrome, which highlights hard water spots. Read more about hard water issues in [how Chandler hard water affects bathroom tile](/blog/chandler-az-hard-water-bathroom-tile/).\n\n### 2. ADA-Compliant Accessibility\nIf you are designing the walk-in shower for universal design or aging-in-place:\n*   **Linear Drains:** Easier to integrate into curbless entries.\n*   **Grab Bars:** Anchor securely to wood studs.\n*   **Shower Seats:** Built-in tiled benches or folding wood benches.\n*   For detailed guidelines on universal shower specs, review our [ADA bathroom requirements in Arizona](/blog/ada-bathroom-requirements-arizona/).\n\n---\n\n## Choosing a Licensed Local Specialist\n\nInstalling a walk-in shower is a high-risk project if done incorrectly. A single pinhole leak in a shower pan can rot your subfloor and cost thousands to repair. Make sure your contractor is licensed, insured, and experienced in custom shower builds:\n*   ARZ Home Remodeling is fully licensed under **ROC #ROC338304**.\n*   We offer a **2-year workmanship warranty** on all custom tile showers.\n*   We handle all building permits through the City of Chandler.\n\nReady to upgrade to a custom walk-in shower? Contact Mike Hernandez and our team of expert Chandler remodelers today at **(520) 569-3339** to discuss your design ideas and schedule your free, itemized project quote.\n  "
