  "updatedAt": "2026-05-10T08:00:00Z",
  "content": "\n# Top Tub-to-Shower Conversion Ideas for Chandler, AZ Homes\n\nBathtubs were once a standard feature in every home. Today, many homeowners find that large garden tubs or old alcove bathtubs are rarely used and difficult to clean. If you are planning a bathroom renovation, a tub-to-shower conversion is a practical upgrade that maximizes usable space, improves accessibility, and updates the look of your home.\n\nIn this guide, we share popular tub-to-shower design ideas and layout tips tailored for Chandler, Arizona homes.\n\n---\n\n## Layout Configurations for Tub Conversions\n\nMost alcove tubs occupy a footprint of **30 inches by 60 inches**. When you remove the tub, you gain an identical area for a custom walk-in shower. Here are the common layouts:\n\n### 1. The Standard Alcove Conversion (30\" x 60\")\n*   **Layout:** The shower footprint matches the old tub.\n*   **Glass:** A sliding glass bypass door or a single fixed glass partition panel.\n*   **Fixtures:** Control valves placed on the plumbing wall, with the shower head positioned to spray away from the opening.\n\n### 2. The Expanded Master Walk-In (42\" x 72\"+)\n*   In master bathrooms, removing a corner garden tub or tub-deck structure allows you to build an expanded walk-in shower.\n*   **Layout:** Curbless entry with a linear drain.\n*   **Aesthetic:** Frameless glass panels that make the bathroom feel twice as large.\n*   For cost details on this configuration, check our [tub to shower conversion](/tub-to-shower-conversion/) page.\n\n---\n\n## Design Ideas for Chandler Desert Homes\n\n### 1. Modern Desert Palette\nEmbrace warm earth tones that complement the Arizona landscape:\n*   **Tile:** Sandstone-look porcelain tile or textured travertine.\n*   **Grout:** Warm gray or tan grout to minimize hard water mineral staining.\n*   **Accents:** Matte black hardware to create a clean, contemporary contrast.\n\n### 2. Universal Access & Aging-in-Place\n*   **Zero-Threshold Entry:** Eliminate the curb for a seamless transition from the bathroom floor into the shower.\n*   **Stud-Anchored Benches:** A built-in tiled bench or a folding teak wood seat.\n*   **Safety Features:** Grab bars that match the style of your other hardware.\n*   For accessible design specifications, see our guide on [ADA bathroom requirements in Arizona](/blog/ada-bathroom-requirements-arizona/).\n\n### 3. Spa-Style Rain Showers\n*   **Fixtures:** A ceiling-mounted rainfall shower head paired with a handheld wand.\n*   **Storage:** Recessed tile niches built into the wall framing for soap and shampoo.\n\n---\n\n## ROI and Resale Considerations\n\nHomeowners often ask: *Will removing my bathtub hurt my home value?*\n*   **The Golden Rule:** Keep at least one bathtub in the house (typically in the guest or hall bathroom) for families with young children.\n*   **Master Bathrooms:** Replacing a garden tub with a large, luxury walk-in shower is highly sought after by buyers and typically yields a strong return on investment.\n*   Read more about budgeting and ROI in our [walk-in shower cost Chandler AZ](/blog/walk-in-shower-cost-chandler-az/) guide.\n\n---\n\n## Getting Started with Your Conversion\n\nConverting a tub to a shower requires updating the plumbing drain lines and installing a complete waterproofing membrane:\n*   ARZ Home Remodeling handles the entire process, from demolition to final inspection.\n*   We use the **Schluter-KERDI waterproofing system** and premium porcelain tile.\n*   We operate under license **ROC #ROC338304** and serve communities across Chandler, Gilbert, and Mesa.\n\nReady to start your tub-to-shower conversion? Contact Mike Hernandez and our team today at **(520) 569-3339** to schedule your free in-home estimate.\n  "
